a.title: Workers
a.desc: Workers are autonomous processes that run one script at a time using the entire cpu and memory available to them.

a.title: Scripts
a.desc: Windmill supports scripts in Python, TypeScript, Go, Bash and Sql.

a.title: Flows
a.desc: Workflows are graphs (DAG) that represent the dependencies between steps.

a.title: Schedules
a.desc: Run scripts and flows at a given frequency.

a.title: Webhooks
a.desc: Each Script and Flow created in Windmill gets autogenerated webhooks.

a.title: Auto-generated UIs
a.desc: Windmill automatically generates user interfaces (UIs) for scripts and flows based on their parameters.

a.title: Apps
a.desc: The app editor is a low-code builder to create custom User Interfaces with a mix of drag-and-drop and code.
